glosses: To take or carry something from one place or side to another

examples.translation: I'm crossing the street with the children

glosses: To put into record, to take down as a note
To place or install something where it is meant to go
To walk someone out, to walk someone to the door when they are leaving, to see out
To spend time doing something or to live or reside at a place for a time
To wear, to put on, often implying that the action is done hastily or carelessly; to slip into
To apply an action on a mass of people or things

examples.text: Baban imparator olabilmek için bütün kardeşlerini kılıçtan geçirdi.
examples.translation: Your father put all his brothers to the sword to become the emperor.

glosses: To cheat someone in a transaction, to rip off
To copy answers from someone else (in a homework sheet, exam etc.)

examples.text: Zamanım az, bu ödevi senden geçirebilir miyim?
examples.translation: I'm low on time, may I copy your answers for this homework?

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish كچورمك (geçirmek, “to make or let enter or pass through or penetrate, to pass into register, to pass off as good, to make or let succeed to a rank”), from Ottoman Turkish كچمك (geçmek, “to pass by, through, along, over, into a thing, to expire, to deteriorate, to have influence, to overlook”), from Proto-Turkic *keč- (“to pass, to wade”).
